name: io.bytes.per.checksum
description:
The number of bytes per checksum.  Must not be larger than
  io.file.buffer.size.

name: fs.s3a.max.total.tasks
description:
The number of operations which can be queued for execution.
  This is in addition to the number of active threads in fs.s3a.threads.max.

name: dfs.journalnode.edits.dir.perm
description:
Permissions for the directories on on the local filesystem where
      the DFS journal node stores the edits. The permissions can either be
      octal or symbolic.

name: dfs.qjournal.select-input-streams.timeout.ms
description: Timeout in milliseconds for accepting streams from JournalManagers.

name: dfs.block.scanner.volume.join.timeout.ms
description:
The amount of time in milliseconds that the BlockScanner times out waiting
    for the VolumeScanner thread to join during a shutdown call.

name: dfs.client.deadnode.detection.probe.deadnode.threads
description: The maximum number of threads to use for probing dead node.

name: dfs.image.transfer.timeout
description:
Socket timeout for the HttpURLConnection instance used in the image
        transfer. This is measured in milliseconds.
        This timeout prevents client hangs if the connection is idle
        for this configured timeout, during image transfer.

name: dfs.client.refresh.read-block-locations.threads
description:
Number of threads to use for refreshing LocatedBlocks of registered
      DFSInputStreams. If a DFSClient opens many DFSInputStreams, increasing
      this may help refresh them all in a timely manner.

name: mapreduce.jobhistory.loadedjobs.cache.size
description:
Size of the loaded job cache.  This property is ignored if
  the property mapreduce.jobhistory.loadedtasks.cache.size is set to a
  positive value.
